'''Owen Olamidayo Goodman''' (born 27 November 2003) is a professional [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{English football updater|Barnsley}} club [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]], on loan from {{English football updater|CrystalP}} club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]]. Born in England, he represents the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada national team]].

==Early life==
Goodman was born in [[London]], England.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-01-28 |title=Profil - Canada Soccer |url=https://canadasoccer.com/fr/profil/ |access-date=2025-12-04 |language=fr-CA}}</ref> He moved to [[Canada]] with his parents when he was five and played for clubs South Simcoe United and County FC in [[Alliston, Ontario]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=2025-07-02 |title=SCOUT REPORT: OWEN GOODMAN |url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2025/july/02/scout-report--owen-goodman/ |archive-date= |access-date= |website=Huddersfield Town AFC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Nightingale |first=Tom |date=2025-03-25 |title=Talented Crystal Palace goalkeeper Owen Goodman says he's 'just waiting on a call-up from Canada' |url=https://canadiansoccerdaily.com/2025/03/25/talented-crystal-palace-goalkeeper-owen-goodman-says-hes-just-waiting-on-a-call-up-from-canada/ |access-date= |website=Canadian Soccer Daily |language=en}}</ref> During this period, he transitioned from playing as a defender to goalkeeper so that he could continue playing after training sessions.<ref name=persist>{{Cite news |last=Kloke |first=Joshua |last2=Woosnam |first2=Matt |date=2025-11-12 |title=Owen Goodman’s persistent path to Canadian citizenship makes him a World Cup wild card |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6801118/2025/11/12/owen-goodman-canada-goalkeeper-world-cup-huddersfield-crystal-palace/ |access-date=2025-11-12 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

He returned to the United Kingdom from Ontario in 2015, at the age of thirteen.<ref name="standard"/><ref>{{Cite web |last=Iles |first=Marc |date=2025-05-20 |title=Bolton Wanderers eyeing Crystal Palace goalkeeper Owen Goodman on loan |url=https://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/sport/25176635.crystal-palace-keeper-owen-goodman-bolton-wanderers-list/ |access-date= |website=The Bolton News |language=en}}</ref> He started playing with the Crystal Palace academy from under-13 level.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2022/11/super-eagles-hopeful-goodman-extends-contract-with-crystal-palace/amp/|location=Lagos, Nigeria|newspaper=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard]]|accessdate=4 June 2023|date=November 16, 2022| title=Super Eagles hopeful, Goodman extends contract with Crystal Palace}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Crystal Palace===
Goodman signed a professional contract with [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] in July 2021 as a seventeen year-old.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allnigeriasoccer.com/read_news.php?nid=40412|website=Allnigeriasoccer.com|accessdate=4 June 2023|title=Another Nigerian goalkeeper signs new deal with English Premier League club|date=July 10, 2021}}</ref>

====2022–23====
Goodman had a place on the first-team bench for Crystal Palace in the [[Premier League]] against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in October 2022.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://guardian.ng/sport/crystal-palace-youth-goalkeeping-sensation-goodman-gets-new-deal/|location=Lagos, Nigeria|newspaper=[[The Guardian (Nigeria)|The Guardian]]|accessdate=4 June 2023|title= Crystal Palace youth goalkeeping sensation, Goodman, gets new deal|first=Michael|last=Egbejule|date=18 November 2022}}</ref> He signed a contract extension with Crystal Palace in November 2022.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://punchng.com/goodman-pens-new-palace-deal/?amp|newspaper=[[The Punch]]|accessdate=4 June 2023|title= Goodman pens new Palace deal|date=17 November 2022|first=Adeyinka|last=Adedipe}}</ref> He made the Palace first-team bench in Premier League away trips to [[Brighton & Hove Albion]], [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/teams/first-team/goalkeeper/owen-goodman/|title=Owen Goodman|accessdate=4 June 2023|website=cpfc}}</ref>

====2023–24: Colchester United (loan)====
In July 2023, Goodman joined [[EFL League Two|League Two]] club [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]] on a season-long [[Loan (sports)#Association football|loan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Owen Goodman: Colchester United sign Crystal Palace goalkeeper on season-long loan|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66208446|date=14 July 2023|accessdate=15 July 2023|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made 40 appearances in all competitions for the club.<ref name=":0" />

====2024–25: AFC Wimbledon (loan)====
On 16 July 2024, Goodman returned to League Two for another loan spell, joining [[AFC Wimbledon]] for the duration of the [[2024–25 AFC Wimbledon season|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.afcwimbledon.co.uk/news/2024/july/16/goodman-dons-the-gloves/|title=Goodman Dons the gloves!|website=www.afcwimbledon.co.uk|date=16 July 2024|accessdate=16 July 2024}}</ref> In September 2024, he saved two penalties in a shoot-out to help Wimbledon knock [[Premier League]] side [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] out of the [[EFL Cup]].<ref name="standard">{{cite web|website=Evening Standard|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/afc-wimbledon-newcastle-carabao-cup-owen-goodman-crystal-palace-b1184943.html|title=  AFC Wimbledon loanee relishing Newcastle test as he targets Crystal Palace future|first=Dom|last=Smith|date=30 September 2024|accessdate=1 October 2024}}</ref> On 26 May 2025, Goodman earned a clean sheet as Wimbledon defeated [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] in the [[2025 EFL League Two play-off final|play-off final]] to earn promotion to [[EFL League One|League One]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Peddy |first=Chris |date=2025-05-26 |title=AFC Wimbledon 1-0 Walsall: Dons promoted to League One |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c62nd4lrlm6t |access-date= |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

During the season, as the first-choice goalkeeper, Goodman featured in every competitive fixture. He was named in the [[EFL Awards#2025 Awards|League Two Team of the Season]] and was awarded the [[EFL Golden Glove|League Two Golden Glove]] after keeping 24 of his 25 clean sheets in the league. His total placed him joint-second for the most clean sheets in a single League Two campaign.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2025-05-28 |title=Loan Report: Owen Goodman wins play-off final with AFC Wimbledon - News |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/club/loan-report-owen-goodman-promoted-afc-wimbledon-play-off-final/ |access-date= |website=Crystal Palace F.C. |language=en-GB}}</ref>

====2025–26: Huddersfield Town (loan)====
On 2 July 2025, Goodman signed for [[EFL League One|League One]] club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] for the duration of the [[2025–26 Huddersfield Town A.F.C. season|2025–26 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cly8jjr9vyno|title=Huddersfield sign Palace keeper Goodman|website=www.bbc.co.uk|date=2 July 2025|accessdate=3 July 2025}}</ref>
On 8 January 2026, Goodman’s loan at Huddersfield Town was terminated early after he made 12 appearances for the club, only six of which came after September 2025.<ref>{{cite web|title=Loan: Owen Goodman returns to Crystal Palace|url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2026/january/08/loan--owen-goodman-returns-to-crystal-palace/|website=Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|date=8 January 2026|access-date=25 May 2026}}</ref><ref name="onesoccer.ca">{{cite web|title=Why Barnsley loan makes sense for CanMNT hopeful Owen Goodman after 25/26 struggles|url=https://onesoccer.ca/a/why-barnsley-loan-makes-sense-for-can-mnt-hopeful-owen-goodman-after-25-26-struggles|website=OneSoccer|date=2026|access-date=25 May 2026}}</ref>

====2026: Barnsley (loan)====
On 15 January 2026, Owen Goodman joined [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] on loan for the remainder of the 2025–26 season following the early termination of his loan at Huddersfield Town. He made his debut two days later in a 2–1 victory over [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Owen Goodman joins on loan until end of season|url=https://www.barnsleyfc.co.uk/news/2026/january/15/owen-goodman-joins-on-loan-until-end-of-season/|website=Barnsley F.C.|date=15 January 2026|access-date=25 May 2026}}</ref><ref name="onesoccer.ca"/>

==International career==
Goodman was eligible to play for [[England national football team|England]], [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]] and [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]].<ref name="standard" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://punchng.com/young-goalie-goodman-commits-future-to-nigeria/ |title=Young goalie Goodman commits future to Nigeria |first=Adeyinka |last=Adedipe |date=21 October 2022 |accessdate=3 August 2023 |newspaper=[[The Punch]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=1-ON-1 🎙️ + SQUAD ANALYSIS: Jesse Marsch calls up CanMNT dual-nationals Alfie Jones, Owen Goodman & Marcelo Flores |url=https://onesoccer.ca/a/jesse-marsch-makes-short-and-long-term-bets-with-can-mnt-dual-nationals-goodman-jones-and-flores |access-date=2025-11-07 |website=onesoccer.ca}}</ref> In 2025 he had expressed his dream of representing Canada's senior national team.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-02 |title=OWEN GOODMAN: "IT'S A PLEASURE TO BE HERE" |url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2025/july/02/owen-goodman---it-s-a-pleasure-to-be-here-/ |access-date= |website=Huddersfield Town AFC}}</ref> In January 2023, Goodman was called up to a [[Nigeria national under-20 football team|Nigeria U-20]] training camp, but ultimately declined.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://scorenigeria.com.ng/crystal-palace-goalkeeper-owen-goodman-shuns-flying-eagles/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230207041812/https://scorenigeria.com.ng/crystal-palace-goalkeeper-owen-goodman-shuns-flying-eagles/|url-status=usurped|archive-date=February 7, 2023|website=scoreng|accessdate=4 June 2023|title= Crystal Palace goalkeeper Owen Goodman shuns Flying Eagles|date=16 January 2023}}</ref>

===England===
Goodman was called up to the [[England national under-18 football team|England U-18]] side in 2021.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://guardian.ng/sport/england-based-18-year-old-goodman-may-end-nigerias-goalkeeping-nightmare/ |location=Lagos, Nigeria|title=England-based 18-year-old Goodman may end Nigeria's goalkeeping nightmare |first=Michael |last=Egbejule |date=20 October 2022 |accessdate=4 June 2023 |newspaper=[[The Guardian (Nigeria)|The Guardian]]}}</ref>  He played for the [[England national under-20 football team|England U-20]] against [[United States men's national under-20 soccer team|USA U-20]] on 25 March 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2023/03/25/world/under-20-friendlies/england-youth/united-states-youth/4058994/|title=ENGLAND U20 VS USA U20 4-2|date=25 March 2023|accessdate=4 June 2023|website=Soccerway}}</ref> In October 2023, he was called up to the England U-20 side for matches against [[Portugal national under-20 football team|Portugal U-20]] and [[Romania national under-20 football team|Romania U-20]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2023/Oct/06/england-mens-elite-league-squad-named-for-romania-and-portugal-games-20230610|website=Englandfootball.com|accessdate=6 October 2023|date=6 October 2023|title= Interim head coach Joe Edwards has picked a 21-man squad for their games with Romania and Portugal in October}}</ref>

On 23 May 2025, Goodman was named to the [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]] pre-EURO training squad.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Veevers |first=Nicholas |date=2025-05-23 |title=England MU21s training squad named for pre-EURO camp |url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2025/May/23/england-mens-under-21s-EURO-training-camp-squad-announced-20252305 |access-date= |website=England Football |language=en}}</ref>

===Canada===
In April 2022, Goodman accepted a call-up to the [[Canada men's national under-20 soccer team|Canada under-20]] team for two friendlies against [[Costa Rica national under-20 football team|Costa Rica]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://northerntribune.ca/canada-u-20-canadian-premier-league-camp/|date=April 5, 2022|title=Six CPL Players Named To Canada U-20 Roster|work=Northern Tribune|first=John|last=Jacques}}</ref>

In August 2025, Canada's coach [[Jesse Marsch]] announced that Goodman was not eligible for Canada's national team, despite their efforts to meet eligibility requirements.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kloke |first=Joshua |date=2025-08-20 |title=Canada’s Jesse Marsch focused on final days of European transfer window |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6562762/2025/08/19/canada-jesse-marsch-world-cup-europe-transfers/ |access-date=2025-08-20 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> However, Goodman had begun pursuing Canadian citizenship earlier that year in March, hiring a lawyer to advance his case, and later declined an approach from [[Nigeria Football Federation|Nigeria]] while awaiting a decision.<ref name="persist" /> After completing the citizenship process in October 2025, he travelled to [[Toronto]] to take his citizenship oath and was subsequently named in Canada's squad for the November 2025 international window for a pair of friendlies against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] and [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://onesoccer.ca/a/jesse-marsch-makes-short-and-long-term-bets-with-can-mnt-dual-nationals-goodman-jones-and-flores|title=1-ON-1 🎙️ + SQUAD ANALYSIS: Jesse Marsch calls up CanMNT dual-nationals Alfie Jones, Owen Goodman & Marcelo Flores|date=November 6, 2025|first=Alexandre|last=Gangué-Ruzic|work=[[OneSoccer]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Press |first=The Canadian |title=Looking for more talent, Canada coach Jesse Marsch brings in three new faces to camp |url=https://chatnewstoday.ca/2025/11/06/canada-coach-jesse-marsch-calls-in-marcelo-flores-alfie-jones-for-november-camp/ |access-date=2025-11-07 |website=CHAT News Today |language=en}}</ref><ref name="persist" />

In May 2026, Goodman was named to Canada's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://northerntribune.ca/world-cup-2026-canada-squad/|first=John|last=Jacques|date=May 29, 2026|title=Here’s The Canada World Cup Roster|work=Northern Tribune}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Goodman has an English father and a Nigerian mother.<ref>{{Cite news|url= https://punchng.com/young-goalie-goodman-commits-future-to-nigeria/?amp|newspaper=[[The Punch]]|accessdate=4 June 2023|first=Adeyinka|last=Adedipe|title= Young goalie Goodman commits future to Nigeria|date=21 October 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thestreetjournal.org/crystal-palace-sensation-makes-u-turn-on-playing-for-england-commits-to-super-eagles/|title=Crystal Palace Sensation Makes U-Turn On Playing For England, Commits To Super Eagles|date=October 29, 2021}}</ref><ref name="standard"/>

